Philippine Stocks: First Gen, Globe, Philippine Long Distance

-- B y   C e c i l i a   Y a p
-- 
2011-05-11T04:27:13Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-11/philippine-stocks-first-gen-globe-philippine-long-distance.html
The Philippine Stock Exchange Index
rose 0.7 percent to 4,335.04 at the noon close in  Manila . The
gauge rose for a third straight day to close at its highest
level since Nov. 5.  The following companies were among the most active. Stock
symbols are in parentheses.  First Gen Corp. (FGEN)   increased 3.3 percent to 15.00
pesos, its biggest gain since April 27. The electricity producer
may build a gas-fired power plant and bid for state assets to
expand its capacity, President Francis Giles Puno told
shareholders in Manila today.  Globe Telecom Inc. (GLO)  , the nation’s second-largest
telecommunications company, rose 4.7 percent to 890 pesos, the
biggest gain since March 31. First-quarter net income increased
1 percent to 3 billion pesos ($70 million), ending four straight
quarters of year-on-year declines.  Philippine Long Distance Telephone Co. (TEL)  , the
nation’s most valuable company, declined 0.7 percent to 2,462
pesos. Net income in the first quarter fell 6 percent to 10.73
billion pesos on lower revenue, the company said in a statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Cecilia Yap in Manila at   cyap19@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Darren Boey at 
 dboey@bloomberg.net  